buttons.snippet: Plant Irish moss in full sun (in cooler climates) or slightly shady spots where you want walkable swaths of green. In small yards, it can even be used as a lawn substitute. buttons.snippet: Best in full sun or part shade, in evenly moist, well-drained soils. Fertilize sparingly to keep the plant compact.
